This is very revealing. Look at line 2572-2574:

```typescript
protected canCollectErrors(): boolean {
    return !this.isReadOnly || settings.readOnly.enableValidation;
}
```

For **questions**, there's already a `canCollectErrors` method that checks `isReadOnly` and skips validation when the question is read-only (unless `settings.readOnly.enableValidation` is set). But for **panels**, the `validateRequired` method (line 995-1006) does NOT check if the panel is read-only.

Let me also check if `canCollectErrors` is overridden in panel.ts

